Comments¶

a) Increase in cement amount increases strength

b) As the age increases strength increases. 28 days seems to optimal to achieve better strength

c) Superplastic improves strength has positive relationship with compression strength

d) Older cements needs more water

Split Train and Test Data¶

In [28]:
X = convertedDF.drop('strength', axis=1)
Y = convertedDF['strength']

#Let's split the data for training and testing
X_train, X_test,Y_train, Y_test = train_test_split(X, Y, test_size=0.30,random_state=7)

Execute Regresssion models and capture accuracy score¶

#Linear Regression
In [30]:
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression #importing linear regression

lr = LinearRegression()

lr.fit(X_train, Y_train)

lr_pred = lr.predict(X_test)  # Predictions from linear regression
lr_score = lr.score(X_test, Y_test)


#dataframe to store score
scoreDF = pd.DataFrame({'Method':['Linear Regression'], 'Accuracy': lr_score},index={'1'})
scoreDF = scoreDF[['Method', 'Accuracy']]
scoreDF

KFold crossvalidation on Linear, Decistion, RandomForst, AdaBoost and Bagging regressors¶

In [39]:
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score
kfold = 10
lr_cv_score = cross_val_score(lr, X_train, Y_train, cv = kfold).mean()
dtr_cv_score = cross_val_score(dtr, X_train, Y_train, cv = kfold).mean()
rfr_cv_score = cross_val_score(rfr, X_train, Y_train, cv = kfold).mean()
abr_cv_score = cross_val_score(abr, X_train, Y_train, cv = kfold).mean()
br_cv_score = cross_val_score(br, X_train, Y_train, cv = kfold).mean()

#dataframe to store score
tempDF = pd.DataFrame({'Method':['Linear Regression CV'], 'Accuracy': lr_cv_score},index={'6'})
scoreDF = pd.concat([scoreDF, tempDF])

tempDF = pd.DataFrame({'Method':['Decision Tree Regressor CV'], 'Accuracy': dtr_cv_score},index={'7'})
scoreDF = pd.concat([scoreDF, tempDF])

tempDF = pd.DataFrame({'Method':['Random Forest Regressor CV'], 'Accuracy': rfr_cv_score},index={'8'})
scoreDF = pd.concat([scoreDF, tempDF])

tempDF = pd.DataFrame({'Method':['AdaBoost Regressor CV'], 'Accuracy': abr_cv_score},index={'9'})
scoreDF = pd.concat([scoreDF, tempDF])

tempDF = pd.DataFrame({'Method':['Bagging Regressor CV'], 'Accuracy': br_cv_score},index={'10'})
scoreDF = pd.concat([scoreDF, tempDF])

scoreDF = scoreDF[['Method', 'Accuracy']]
scoreDF

Parameter Tuning¶

Lets use RandomizedSearchCV to improve accuracy on Random Forest Regressor and Bagging Regressor

In [41]:
#RandomizedSearchCV on RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.model_selection import RandomizedSearchCV

parameters = {'bootstrap': [True],
 'max_depth': [10, 20, 30, 40, 50],
 'max_features': ['auto', 'sqrt'],
 'min_samples_leaf': [1, 2, 4, 8],
 'n_estimators': [100]}


rfr_rscv = RandomizedSearchCV(RandomForestRegressor(), parameters, cv = 5, n_jobs= 4)
rfr_rscv.fit(X_train, Y_train)

rfr_rscv.best_params_
Out[41]:
{'n_estimators': 100,
 'min_samples_leaf': 1,
 'max_features': 'sqrt',
 'max_depth': 10,
 'bootstrap': True}
In [42]:
#Lets apply the parameters to RandomForestRegressor with cross validation to see if the accuarcy is improved
rfr_with_param_tuning = RandomForestRegressor(bootstrap= True,
 max_depth= 40,
 max_features= 'auto',
 min_samples_leaf= 1,
 n_estimators= 100)


rfr_with_param_tuning_cv_score = cross_val_score(rfr_with_param_tuning, X_train, Y_train, cv = 5).mean()


#dataframe to store score
paramTuningScoreDF = pd.DataFrame({'Method':['Random Forest Regressor'], 'Accuracy': rfr_with_param_tuning_cv_score},index={'1'})
paramTuningScoreDF = paramTuningScoreDF[['Method', 'Accuracy']]
paramTuningScoreDF
